{"word":"κλυδώνιον","slug":"κλυδώνιον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κλυδώνιον</b></el> <el>(κλῠδώνιον, ου, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Diminutive'>Dim.</a> of <a href='S:κλύδων'><el>κλύδων</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a little wave, ripple</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; generally, <i>a wave</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—as collective noun, <i>the surf</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>κλ. χολῆς</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}